# Development Standards & Guidelines

## Code Quality Standards

### TypeScript Configuration
- **Strict Mode:** Enabled for type safety
- **Interfaces:** All types defined in [types/index.ts](mdc:types/index.ts)
- **Type Safety:** Use existing interfaces and create new ones as needed
- **Compile Errors:** Currently ignored during builds for Capacitor compatibility

### ESLint Configuration
- **Code Quality:** Run `npm run lint` before committing
- **Build Ignore:** Linting ignored during builds for mobile assets
- **Standards:** Follow Next.js ESLint configuration

## File Naming Conventions

### App Router Files
- **Pages:** `page.tsx` (required for routes)
- **Layouts:** `layout.tsx` (shared layouts)
- **Loading:** `loading.tsx` (loading states)
- **Error:** `error.tsx` (error boundaries)

### Components
- **UI Components:** PascalCase (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `ProductCard.tsx`)
- **Business Components:** PascalCase with descriptive names
- **Hooks:** camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)

### Directories
- **Routes:** kebab-case (e.g., `control_panel/`, `client/`)
- **Components:** kebab-case directories, PascalCase files
- **Services:** camelCase (e.g., `convex/services/`)

## Component Patterns

### Props Interfaces
```typescript
// Use existing interfaces from types/index.ts
interface ButtonProps {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost";
  size?: "xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  disabled?: boolean;
  loading?: boolean;
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

### Error Handling
```typescript
// Always use try-catch with user-friendly messages
try {
  await someAsyncOperation();
} catch (error) {
  const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'An error occurred';
  setError(message);
}
```

## State Management Rules

### Zustand Stores
- **Global State:** Auth and cart in [store/](mdc:store/)
- **Persistence:** Use localStorage for auth and cart data
- **TypeScript:** Strict typing for all store interfaces

### Convex Integration
- **Queries:** Use reactive queries for real-time data
- **Mutations:** Use mutations for data modifications
- **Actions:** Use actions for external API calls

## Business Logic Requirements

### User Support
- **Dual Mode:** Support both authenticated users and guests
- **Guest Sessions:** Auto-generated guest IDs for non-authenticated users
- **Role-Based Access:** Implement proper authorization checks

### E-commerce Features
- **Cart Functionality:** Full cart management for users and guests
- **Reservations:** Multi-item reservation system for live fish
- **Order Processing:** Complete order workflow with status tracking

## Mobile Compatibility

### Responsive Design
- **Mobile-First:** Design for mobile screens first
- **Touch Targets:** Ensure proper touch target sizes
- **Performance:** Optimize for mobile performance

### Capacitor Integration
- **Build Process:** Follow Capacitor build requirements
- **Static Export:** Use `out/` directory for mobile assets
- **Development:** Run dev server on `0.0.0.0:3000` for mobile testing

## Testing & Quality Assurance

### Manual Testing
- **User Flows:** Test both authenticated and guest user flows
- **Mobile Testing:** Test on mobile devices and emulators
- **Cross-Platform:** Verify web and mobile functionality

### Code Review Checklist
- [ ] TypeScript types are properly defined
- [ ] Components follow established patterns
- [ ] Error handling is implemented
- [ ] Mobile compatibility is maintained
- [ ] Both user types (authenticated/guest) are supported
- [ ] Business logic is preserved
- [ ] Performance is optimized